<h2>1. The "Negative Space" Strategy: Reading Reviews Between the Lines</h2>
<p>Most hosts just look at the star rating. A 4.8-star guest looks fine, right? <strong>Wrong.</strong> In the Airbnb community, "Review Inflation" is real. We look for "polite warnings" like <em>"They were communicative throughout the stay"</em> (Translation: They complained about everything) or <em>"Better suited for guests who don't prioritize cleanliness"</em> (Translation: They left the place a disaster).</p>

